title: Which K-pop idols overshadow their groups? - Quora

There are some groups that have members with much more CFs, screen time, and center positions. Then there are some members who really stand out amongst other members. I decided to include only 3rd and 4th generation idols (I don’t know a lot about 1st or 2nd gen), so groups such as AOA or Big Bang won’t be here. Momoland JooE: I think that JooE is way more popular than her other Momoland members because she has a bright personality really fit for idols and TV shows. She is likable, remembered, and she also has a lot of CFs. Iz*one Chaeyeon: Chaeyeon is extremely popular and oftentimes gets 1st place in popularity rankings. (She’s my bias!) Although she doesn’t really get that much screentime or lines, her bubbly and cute personality and amazing dance ability really seem to captivate the audience. Everglow Mia: Nowadays, I feel like Everglow has become “Mia and friends.” She gets literally over half of the lines in a song, with a ton of screentime and center. In Dun Dun, she also got a dance break. So I think it is safe to say that Mia is somewhat overshadowing Everglow. Blackpink Jennie: Another idol who is way favored than her bandmates. Jennie usually gets first or second place in lines and screentime, she can break rules and still be excused, and she got a freaking SOLO just two years after debut, when Blackpink were still considered rookies. Red Velvet Irene: Irene is known worldwide for her insane visuals, with nicknames such as “visual goddess” and “CF queen”. She gets more offers for commercials, modeling ads, and variety programs. So it’s no wonder she’s the most popular in Red Velvet. Mamamoo Hwasa: Hwasa is popular, either good or bad. She gets praised for her strong woman empowerment and for challenging the Korean norm with her visuals and strong vocals. On the other hand, she is also famous for getting into many fashion scandals. She became even more popular after her single “Twit” came out. Apink Naeun: Again, Naeun is known for her stunning visuals. “Son Naeun” is probably one of the most familiar and heard names in kpop. (G)-idle Soyeon: Soyeon gets a lot of love as a producing queen and rap goddess of the 4th generation. She has great stage presence and leadership, with almost always placing first in lines and screentime. BTS Jungkook or V: Personally I find it quite hard to find a BTS stan whose bias ISN’T Jungkook or V. These two idols are way more popular than their other members. This could be because the two have stunning visuals and Jungkook has way more screentime and lines.  NCT Taeyong: Taeyong has comparatively very many screentime and lines. He also has great, sexy visuals and a hilarious personality. BTOB Sungjae: Sungjae is famous for his ideal Korean male visuals. He also became an overnight sensation after having one of the main roles in the hit drama “Goblin.” Many people know BTOB because of Sungjae. Wannaone Daniel: Daniel was the nation’s pick and he grew insanely in popularity rankings, rivaling some of the top boy groups at the time. He obviously got a lot of center as Wannaone’s center, and his solo was well received as well. That’s it for today! Please keep in mind that I love all these idols and am in no way bashing them.

lemme put this in bold for all the people who don't read lolol. 🟥➡️This is in my opinion. It is not to say that they are better than their members. This is me saying that they get the most attention(from my pov). everyone is gonna agree and more of all are gonna disagree. A lot of this comes from and outsiders pov. Please keep in my this is my opinion. GDragon (BIGBANG)  I am not a fan of BigBang. Frankly I was a child when they were popular. (not really sure? i remember hearing their songs because they were popular in america n stuff) But G-Dragon always seems to be the most beloved or liked member of the group. Everyone in the group is well known but I do feel like GDragon is a name commonly brought up when people talk about k-pop. Woozi (SEVENTEEN)  I am not a fan of Seventeen. I only know two of their songs. They were one of the first kpop groups I listened to. But I didn't know at the time how much they go into making their songs. I think that Woozi is the 16th male kpop star to have the most copyrights. I know that he is a respected producer and it's pretty well known amongst kpop stans. From what I have seen. Jennie (BLACKPINK)  Jennie is admired for her looks, talents and personality. I think many people say she is YG's favorite. I think that Jennie is well known thanks to her solo single. Even people who aren't kpop stans know her. Many people portray her to be selfish or mean. But watching Jennie more closely,I see her as caring funny and likable. She is supportive towards her members and devoted. Somi (Formerly IOI + Solo Career)  You may recognize Somi for two reasons. Her appearances on Produce 101 or her solo career. I know her for her solo career and her popularity amongst kpop-stans. I am not very educated on IOI or Produce 101. But during her time there from what I am seen she was the center and star of the group. Or at least what management wanted her to be. She is known for her accomplishments for being so young an already having a solo career. But that's just what I have seen. Taeyong (NCT)  Taeyong to me is a great performer. It's not that the other members aren't good because any and everyone from NCT is great. It's just that there is something about him that stands about amongst the crowd. I don't think it's it's visuals or his rapping or smth. I think it's just him when he is on the stage. It's unique and I wish I had that. He is eye catching even if he doesn't try to be. He is very popular in the kpop community and his face has become recognizable amongst most kpop stans. Joo-E (MOMOLAND)  To me,her stage presence prevails amongst others around her. Momoland to nowadays is seen as you everyday girl group stereotype. But JooE takes that and makes it her own. It's like she is a whole new person in and off stage completely. I think she has a lot of potential because of that. Yeonjun (TOMORROWXTOGETHER)  (plsss i love this photo a little too much lolol) I think that at first Yeonjun was never an extremely popular member of TXT. I think that when they first debuted it was Huening Kai. But shortly afterwards in 2020, Yeonjun stole the show. lol. All of the members are very talented to be so young. And Yeonjun is not an exception. People consider him one of the it-boys of the 4th generation. And at times it really shows. Kai (EXO)  Y'all, I don't need to explain myself. He's Kai. I mean he has to be one of the most popular K-pop stars out there. And I feel like everyone loves him. (I mean i do too lol). He is a very good performer. I wish I was cool like him lol he is like a super hero. I think that everyone has equal fame in EXO but Kai is always brought up in topics more recently. Anyways, y'all already know anyone from EXO is popular. Heck, they could all be on the list but we don't have time for that. Meaning you don't have that much time to read and I don't have that much time to write. Anyways that's it. Thank you for reading this took me a long time. Sorry for grammar and spelling errors.

My answers don't mean that I hate any of these idols, I actually love all of them and these are just my opinions Jennie (Blackpink)  Jennie is a sweetheart and I love her, she is literally the cutest lil bean☺❤ Jennie is favored by YG and often receives the most attention and the best treatment from him. She always gets the best clothes and make and is promoted the most out of the other three members. She is the only member with a solo song and she gets away with more things compared to the other members. She is also an ambassador for Chanel.   Lisa (Blackpink)  I absolutely l o v e Lisa❤❤she is the definition of adorable. She's so friendly and loving towards everyone and everything. Even though she doesn't get the same treatment Jennie does, theres still some favoritism that the public gives her. If you aren't a kpop fan but you love fashion and makeup, chances are you've probably heard of either Jennie Kim or Lisa at least once, never Rosé or Jisoo. Lisa was popularized by the public for her fashion and dance skills. She was spotted at a Celine fashion show and pretty much became a fashion icon after that. She's been on magazine covers and she preforms dances for a popular YouTube channel   Yeji (ITZY)  Ah yes, the beautiful Hwang Yeji☺☺she is fierce on stage and a total kitten everywhere else❤She is known for her sharp dance skills and her undeniable beauty. But idk if this is just me or not but I feel like sometimes she gets more opportunities to shine than the other four members do. She gets the most lines and is always in front during their performances. She's always in the middle and the attention always seems to go to her. (No hate, I love Yeji❤❤)    Cha Eun Woo (ASTRO)  Eun Woo😭😭❤❤❤I love him so much he's such a cute lil puppy and he's literally the kindest person you'll ever meet. He's known for being gorgeous lmao (also for his impeccable acting skills) Chances are when you first found out of Cha Eun Woo, you most likely didn't know that he was a singer in a whole ass group. (At least I didn't) You probably knew him for his acting first since he's had a lot of roles in several k-dramas. Eun Woo is promoted a whole hell of a lot more than the other members of ASTRO. His group is relatively small in terms of popularity compared to other groups like EXO, SEVENTEEN, GOT7 etc. The only popular thing about ASTRO is Cha Eun Woo   Lastly…..Jungkook (BTS)  Kookieee!!!💜💜💜he's our little bunny and baby☺I love Jungkook so much, he's literally the cutest person ever. Jungkook is, in my opinion, the most popular and promoted member of BTS. He's the most popular in terms of being everyone's bias and he often gets a lot of attention, both good and bad. He's constantly in front during their live performances and he gets the most lines out of the other six members. He's popularized mostly by the public rather than the company. Jungkook is good at pretty much everything which naturally would bring a lot of attention to oneself, but sometimes I feel like he is over hyped (please don't attack me, I love Jungkook). I love that he is good at a lot of things but it often overshadows the abilities and skills of the other members. Too much pressure is put on him to be perfect    That's all, sorry for the longs answer😁💜 Pls be safe and healthy💜💜💜💜💜 (I'm trying to start a space of my own so a few followers would be a nice addition☺💜)

Overshadow, is causing someone or something to seem less important or noticeable. This situation in Kpop, happens when the group’s agency gives a particular member more screen time, lines, or outfits that makes the member stand out, CFs etc or the member has always been popular from the start. The particular member has more popularity and stronger fan base than the the other members. Unfair treatment can sometimes cause conflits between idols and their companies and even their own fandom. Let’s start! Chaeyeon, Dia Chaeyeon is best known for finishing 7th in the survival show Produce 101, making her a member of I.O.I, a project group formed by Mnet. She is also the lead actress on the web drama, ‘I am’ and ‘my first first love’. Dia has always been mistreated by their company, MBK entertainment. They are also know as Chaeyeon and the others. The two members, Somyi and Yebin also talked about the mistreatement in the show ‘the unit’ and how they were envious of Chaeyeon. ‘Even the articles are all about Chaeyeon. Everything begins and ends with Chaeyeon.’ - Yeebin, Dia This year they had a comeback on June 10th with their mini album, ‘flower 4 seasons’ and the title track ‘hug u’. It is known that Chaeyeon and the member, Somyi both are on a hiatus. This might be a step from MK entertainment to balance out the popularity and to let the other members shine.  JooE, Momoland JooE always stood out to me in Momoland. She has this fun, talkative, sunshine, class clown personality. She is very energetic and has a cheerful vibe. JooE is also the most popular member of Momoland, second being Nancy. Her visuals are also unique in the Kpop industry. Her popularity is mostly based on the criticism given to her by the public for her visuals. Momoland might not be popular in Korea but they are a well known group in the Philippines and internationally. She is best known for her dance in "Wonderful Love EDM Ver".  Cha Eun Woo, ASTRO Cha Eun Woo is famous for his ethereal visuals. He is also known for his lead role as ‘Do kyung Seok’ in the hit drama ‘my id is gangam beauty’. He is literally hated by antis for being more popular than his members, which is not even his fault. It’s hard to admit but the truth is half of the people who know about ASTRO, got to know them because of Cha Eun Woo and I am one of those people. But it’s also no secret that, ASTRO is a talented but underrated group and that people need to stop sleeping on them. I recently just woke up and i regret not realizing that they weren’t a bed.  Soyeon, Gidle The truth is Soyeon is favored by Cube. It’s obvious since she mostly gets the most screen time, and lines, even if she is not the lead or main vocalist.
